President Donald J. Trump has announced the appointment of Kayleigh McEnany as the White House Press Secretary and Alyssa Farah as the Director of Strategic Communications. McEnany is currently serving as the National Press Secretary for Donald J. Trump for President, while Farah is the Press Secretary for the Department of Defense. Ben Williamson, who is currently a Senior Advisor to the White House Chief of Staff, will also join McEnany and Farah as a Senior Communications Advisor.